# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Environment Configuration — AI School
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values.
# The app uses a Supabase-compatible backend (Lovable Cloud, 
# Supabase, or Memfire) and a provider-abstracted AI layer.

# ── Database / Backend ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Point these to your Supabase-compatible instance.
# For Memfire: use your Memfire project URL and anon key.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://your-project.supabase.co"
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="your-anon-key"
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID="your-project-id"

# ── AI / LLM (Edge Function Secrets) ───────────────────────────
# These are configured as backend secrets, NOT in .env.
# Set them via your backend's secret management.
#
# AI_PROVIDER             — "lovable" (default) or "aliyun"
# LOVABLE_API_KEY         — Auto-provisioned for Lovable AI gateway
# DASHSCOPE_API_KEY       — Required only when AI_PROVIDER=aliyun
#
# To migrate to Aliyun DashScope:
#   1. Set secret DASHSCOPE_API_KEY with your Aliyun key
#   2. Set secret AI_PROVIDER to "aliyun"
#   3. Redeploy ai-chat — done, no code changes needed.
